OAK RIDGE, Tenn. (AP) â€” The Roane State Community College Dental Hygiene Clinic in Tennessee is offering free dental cleanings for children ages 4 to 12.The children will receive cleaning, necessary dental X-rays and a fluoride treatment at no charge, the school said. The free cleaning offer is only available through the end of March.The clinic, on the Oak Ridge Branch Campus, is open 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday through Thursday and 8 a.m. to noon Friday. Availability is limited. To make an appointment, call the clinic.The clinic also offers cleanings, sealants and teeth whitening for adults. The facility is closed from May through August.